President Donald J. Trump will award the Medal of Honor to Ronald J. Shurer II on October 1, 2018. Shurer, a former Staff Sergeant in the United States Army, will receive the Medal of Honor for his actions on April 6, 2008, while serving as a Senior Medical Sergeant. He treated and stabilized injured soldiers while under enemy fire and evacuated them to safety. Shurer's heroic actions saved the lives of his teammates. Shurer enlisted in the Army in 2002 and served in Afghanistan from 2007 to 2008. He was honorably discharged in 2009 and later joined the Secret Service. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate great personal bravery and self-sacrifice at the risk of their own lives.